---
title: Make-Ahead Spinach & Potato Frittata with Pepper Jack, Italian Cheese Blend & Sundried Tomato Aioli
description: This hearty vegetarian breakfast bake takes its cue from classic Spanish tortilla, a beloved egg-and-potato dish. Ours is fully loaded with leafy spinach, savory-sweet caramelized onion, and melty cheese. A simple sundried tomato aïoli makes a savory dip or sauce for this make-ahead marvel that’s perfect for any time of day, any day of the week!

*This recipe is triple the typical servings, providing 6 servings and 12 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.*
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/663132f10fc5c011176b0d0a-074e7159.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/663132f10fc5c011176b0d0a-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Southern Europe
servings: 2
time required: 50 minutes
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 360 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 16 g
  sugar: 3 g
  protein: 13 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 520 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/make-ahead-spinach-potato-frittata-663132f10fc5c011176b0d0a
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise, then slice into 1/4-inch-thick pieces.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain and set aside.

While potatoes cook, halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add @spinach{5%ounce}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tsp} and a splash of water to pan with onion.

Cook until spinach is wilted and onion is caramelized, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @sour cream{3%tbsp}, 1/4 cup water, 3/4 tsp salt, and pepper until well combined.

Whisk in @eggs{6} until completely incorporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Wash and dry whisk (you'll use it again in Step 6).

Stir in drained potatoes, spinach and onion mixture, and @Italian Cheese Blend{1/2%cup}. (It's OK if the veggies are still hot!)

Coat an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} with @nonstick cooking spray{}.

Pour egg mixture into prepared #baking dish{} and evenly top with @Pepper Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}.

Bake on top rack until eggs are set and cooked through and cheese is lightly browned, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While frittata bakes, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{1%ounce} and @Mayonnaise{4%tbsp} until smooth.

Cover with #plastic wrap{} and refrigerate until ready to serve.

Let frittata cool for ~{5%minutes}, then cut into 6 pieces.

> To serve: Divide frittata between plates and serve with aioli on the side.

> To stash: Let frittata cool completely. Refrigerate frittata and aioli in separate airtight containers for up to 3 days. Reheat in the microwave for 1-2 minutes.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.